;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Knobs\"\n        title=\"Knobs\"\n        src=\"/static/6499d76979cc3daa7ebe9abbac4d6a93/e5166/knobs.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6499d76979cc3daa7ebe9abbac4d6a93/f93b5/knobs.jpg 300w,\n/static/6499d76979cc3daa7ebe9abbac4d6a93/b4294/knobs.jpg 600w,\n/static/6499d76979cc3daa7ebe9abbac4d6a93/e5166/knobs.jpg 1200w,\n/static/6499d76979cc3daa7ebe9abbac4d6a93/ac99c/knobs.jpg 1536w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>(A) <strong>Carriage handwheel</strong>: moves the carriage large distances along the lathe's length</li>\n<li>(B) <strong>Cross feed handwheel</strong>: moves the tool in and out perpendicularly to the Carriage handwheel's motion</li>\n<li>(C) <strong>Half-nut Lever</strong>: engages the auto feeder</li>\n<li>(D) <strong>Carriage lock screw</strong>: locks the carriage's position along the lathe's length.</li>\n<li>(E) <strong>Tool post slide handwheel</strong>: used for fine movements along the length of the lathe while taking off material</li>\n<li>(F) <strong>Tool post</strong>: holds the tool which is shown by letter H</li>\n<li>(G) <strong>Locking Lever</strong>: locks the tool in place so it can not move</li>\n<li>(H) <strong>Tool</strong>: an attachment that can be swapped out for a different use</li>\n<li>(I) <strong>Compound Rest</strong>: the assembly that slides around on top of the carriage</li>\n<li>(J) <strong>Carriage</strong>: the base assembly of the lathe which only moves along the lathe's length</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"videowrapper\">\n  <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/ApenjhgJFNc?rel=0&showinfo=0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"path":"/resources/courses/lathe","title":"Lathe Training"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["3